Texts.Eng: A keyboard instrument that plucks strings, instead of hitting wires.
Texts.Chs: 一种拨弦而不是敲击电线的键盘乐器。

Texts.Eng: A musical frivolity that best describes the excesses of life in the Miniknog's immediate circle.
Texts.Chs: 一种音乐上的轻浮，最好地描述了生活在科技发展部的直接圈子里的过度。

Texts.Eng: All of a sudden I am feeling the urge to dance...my paws too. Music anyone?
Texts.Chs: 突然间我有了跳舞的冲动……我的爪子也跳了起来。有人听音乐吗？

Texts.Eng: Big wooden box makessss lotssss of noissse!
I can't bring myself to think of what tunes should be played on this device.
Texts.Chs: 我想不起在这个设备上应该播放什么曲子。

Texts.Eng: I suppose I could try to play this contraption.
Texts.Chs: 我想我可以试着玩这个玩意儿。

Texts.Eng: In space, nobody can hear the music of the spheres - until you play this!
Texts.Chs: 在太空中，没有人能听到球体的音乐——除非你播放这个！

Texts.Eng: Isn't this musical instrument too anachronistic to be in a futuristic space setting?
Texts.Chs: 在未来的空间环境中，这种乐器不是太过时了吗？

Texts.Eng: Looks like some sort of Human musical instrument
Texts.Chs: 看起来像某种人类乐器

Texts.Eng: Music cannot soothe that breast made savage by the Dark Side.
Texts.Chs: 音乐无法抚慰被黑暗面摧残的乳房。

Texts.Eng: Sure looks like a piano, but it ain't one!
Texts.Chs: 看起来像架钢琴，但不是！

Texts.Eng: The music that could be performed on this keyboard instrument fell out of date many aeons ago.
Texts.Chs: 可以用这种键盘乐器演奏的音乐在很久以前就过时了。

Texts.Eng: This looks to be an Apex attempt to replicate antique Human musical sensibilities.
Texts.Chs: 这看起来是猿族试图复制古代人类的音乐情感。

Texts.Eng: Why in the Slip would anyone dream of playing music on this?
Texts.Chs: 为什么会有人梦想在这上面演奏音乐？
